[thinking] I'm considering whether we should advise using real JDK ML-DSA keys instead of fake ones. Is that part of the "test-code setup guidance"? It seems the current tests create a stub for MlDsaPublicKey that doesn't implement AsymmetricKey, which leads to context failures. Real JDK 25 public keys implement this interface, so I'll need generated tests to use a real KeyPairGenerator. But isn't this just usage guidance rather than setup? It feels a bit complex!
